WEBVTT

00:03.753 --> 00:06.755
SARAH [VOICE-OVER]: In the future,
my son will lead mankind...

00:06.923 --> 00:09.299
...in a war against Skynet.

00:09.759 --> 00:13.512
A computer system programmed
to destroy the world.

00:14.514 --> 00:17.433
It has sent machines
back through time.

00:17.726 --> 00:19.059
Some to kill him.

00:19.394 --> 00:20.894
One to protect him.

00:21.271 --> 00:24.773
Today we fight to stop Skynet
from ever being created.

00:24.941 --> 00:27.401
To change our future.

00:27.569 --> 00:29.862
To change his fate.

00:30.447 --> 00:34.366
The war to save mankind begins now.

00:39.873 --> 00:42.624
NARRATOR: Previously on Terminator:
The Sarah Connor Chronicles....

00:48.089 --> 00:50.716
SARAH: Where are we?
CAMERON: Same where. Different when.

00:51.134 --> 00:52.926
I want my new name.
My whole new me.

00:53.094 --> 00:54.094
I'll track down Enrique.

00:54.262 --> 00:55.512
I need three sets of papers.

00:55.680 --> 00:57.973
My nephew has taken over the business.

00:58.141 --> 01:00.350
-You're in the system and everything.
SARAH: Uncle Enrique would be proud.

01:00.518 --> 01:02.478
[SPEAKING SPANISH]

01:02.645 --> 01:04.813
He referred to you as a rata. Snitch.

01:06.149 --> 01:08.192
-Why would you do this?
CAMERON: Because you wouldn't.

01:08.359 --> 01:12.613
-Why not stay in the past?
-You died two years ago. Cancer.

01:12.781 --> 01:14.990
SARAH: I've seen that before.
CAMERON: Skynet work camp.

01:15.158 --> 01:16.283
Resistance fighters.

01:16.451 --> 01:18.660
JOHN: You sure there's money here?
CAMERON: Anything they valued.

01:18.828 --> 01:20.746
Money. Guns. It would be hidden.

01:24.959 --> 01:26.293
SARAH:
You told me we'd be safe.

01:26.544 --> 01:28.462
CAMERON:
Skynet doesn't know you're here.

01:28.630 --> 01:30.172
There's no directive to hunt you.

01:31.174 --> 01:33.342
What if they found out?
Would they all know what to do?

01:33.510 --> 01:35.469
Who the hell are you, man?

01:36.304 --> 01:37.679
Ah--

01:38.681 --> 01:39.681
CAMERON:
They do.

01:42.977 --> 01:46.271
When I was in the mental hospital
I became obsessed with science.

01:46.815 --> 01:48.357
Not all science, actually.

01:48.942 --> 01:51.151
And not really science at all.

01:51.319 --> 01:54.863
Scientists, and then
only nuclear scientists.

01:55.031 --> 01:56.657
The ones who invented the bomb.

01:58.535 --> 02:01.203
Oppenheimer, Heisenberg,
Fermi and Teller.

02:01.371 --> 02:04.456
Pioneers. Geniuses all.

02:04.666 --> 02:08.043
I read every book I could.
I wanted to understand.

02:08.211 --> 02:12.548
Why couldn't they stop?
These fathers of our destruction?

02:12.882 --> 02:15.008
And why wouldn't anybody
stop them?

02:17.887 --> 02:21.390
And if I had the chance, would I?

02:22.267 --> 02:23.642
[MEN GRUNTING]

03:17.780 --> 03:19.406
Good morning.

03:20.617 --> 03:23.911
-You look like hell.
-Up late.

03:24.746 --> 03:29.208
Newspaper clippings,
surveillance photos, bank records.

03:29.375 --> 03:31.877
Pamphlets from every high-tech company
in the state.

03:32.045 --> 03:34.922
Even thought I saw the deeds
to city hall in here somewhere.

03:35.089 --> 03:39.051
Those Resistance guys weren't sent
back here to be our support crew.

03:39.219 --> 03:40.719
They're a Skynet hunting party.

03:42.472 --> 03:43.722
Really? Are you sure?

03:44.098 --> 03:48.101
Most of this is still a puzzle to me,
but there is one list in here I understand.

03:48.269 --> 03:51.271
Employee list, Cyberdyne Systems.

03:51.981 --> 03:55.943
Seems they thought
it was a good place to start. And it is.

03:56.110 --> 03:57.861
She's not gonna be happy to see you.

03:59.280 --> 04:00.364
She never is.

04:00.990 --> 04:04.159
-You want me to come along?
-No. You have your own job to do.

04:04.369 --> 04:06.119
A big one.

04:15.880 --> 04:18.173
You're getting pretty good at that.

04:18.841 --> 04:20.509
Thank you.

04:23.012 --> 04:25.347
Still, it's not brain surgery
or anything.

04:25.515 --> 04:29.017
It would be funny if you were some
advanced cybernetic intelligence...

04:29.185 --> 04:32.271
...yet stumped by a stick of eyeliner.

04:32.438 --> 04:34.022
No, it's not brain surgery.

04:35.525 --> 04:38.694
Would have to be a lot sharper
for brain surgery.

04:46.869 --> 04:48.537
Much better.

04:48.871 --> 04:52.457
When you wear clothes, much better.

04:53.334 --> 04:56.169
Okay, six ways in, six ways out.

04:56.337 --> 04:59.006
The front opens to the street here.
Security's minimal.

04:59.173 --> 05:01.883
Two armed guards in the morning.
Four in the afternoon.

05:02.051 --> 05:04.553
If anything goes wrong,
there's a parking lot here.

05:04.721 --> 05:09.850
Mom, it's high school, okay?
Not supermax. We can handle it.

05:11.519 --> 05:13.228
We can handle it.

05:13.896 --> 05:15.439
Don't you kiss me.

05:19.319 --> 05:20.402
Or anyone else.

05:23.990 --> 05:27.326
JOHN: Okay, now blend in.
CAMERON: Blend in.

05:27.493 --> 05:30.746
Yeah, I mean don't seem like a freak.
You know what I mean, right?

05:30.913 --> 05:34.916
Freak. Weirdo. Kook.
Oddball. Crackpot.

05:35.084 --> 05:38.378
Strange duck. Queer potato.
Nut.

05:38.546 --> 05:40.380
I've been reading the dictionary.

05:40.548 --> 05:42.758
-I don't sleep.
-That's what I'm talking about.

05:42.967 --> 05:46.428
You do that, you sound like a freak.
Don't walk around like my bodyguard.

05:46.596 --> 05:48.764
You're supposed to be my sister.

05:50.016 --> 05:51.725
You won't fool anyone.

05:53.227 --> 05:55.103
I fooled you.

05:55.772 --> 05:57.272
[SCOFFS]

06:03.446 --> 06:05.072
What's that all about?

06:05.782 --> 06:09.368
Appears to be a re-imagining
of a trompe l'oeil fresco.

06:10.620 --> 06:11.787
I don't sleep.

06:15.083 --> 06:19.544
Cell phones, hats, rings, and bling.
Take it off and put it in the basket.

06:19.712 --> 06:23.382
Cell phones, hats, rings, and bling
in the basket.

06:23.549 --> 06:25.050
In the basket, people. Come on.

06:25.635 --> 06:27.135
The line keeps moving. Let's go.

06:27.303 --> 06:31.223
Cell phones, hats, rings, and bling
in the basket.

06:31.391 --> 06:32.474
Keep the line moving.

06:32.642 --> 06:35.977
Cell phones, caps, rings, and bling
in the basket please.

06:36.145 --> 06:40.148
Let's go. Come on. Thank you.
Cell phones, caps, rings, and bli--

06:41.609 --> 06:43.402
GUARD 1:
Again with you, missy.

06:43.820 --> 06:46.822
Cell phones, hats, rings and bling
in the basket.

06:47.031 --> 06:48.782
GUARD 2: Hold that. Come through.
MAN 1: Come on.

06:48.950 --> 06:50.325
Come on, we ain't got all day.

06:50.493 --> 06:51.660
[SIGHS]

06:52.412 --> 06:54.663
Excuse me. This is my sister.

06:54.831 --> 06:55.997
Extra credit for you.

06:56.165 --> 06:58.667
JOHN: Look, she's got
a metal plate in her head.

06:58.835 --> 07:00.043
Really. It's a big one.

07:01.671 --> 07:03.088
[BEEPING]

07:03.256 --> 07:05.841
MAN 2: Look at this. All right,
metal head, let's go through.

07:06.634 --> 07:08.552
I fell. Hard.

07:09.679 --> 07:11.263
All right, let's go. Go ahead.

07:11.431 --> 07:13.682
Cell phones, caps.

07:24.610 --> 07:28.363
TARISSA: I thought you were dead.
-Well, I'm not.

07:29.615 --> 07:31.491
Lucky you.

07:32.076 --> 07:33.702
-You look--
-Different?

07:33.870 --> 07:35.203
The same.

07:35.371 --> 07:39.708
-Well, I can't explain.
-I wouldn't want you to.

07:41.294 --> 07:44.171
-Is John--?
-He's good.

07:45.089 --> 07:47.340
TARISSA:
What about that machine?

07:48.217 --> 07:49.551
She's still around.

07:50.511 --> 07:52.137
Not that one.

07:52.305 --> 07:54.139
-The other.
-No.

07:56.976 --> 07:58.101
Do you mind?

07:59.145 --> 08:00.896
You brought it.

08:05.693 --> 08:07.360
Danny's not here?

08:08.571 --> 08:10.822
It's ten years, right?

08:11.991 --> 08:14.117
He's at school.

08:14.535 --> 08:17.913
-He hasn't come in a long time.
-I'm sorry to hear that.

08:21.876 --> 08:23.835
What do you want, Sarah?

08:24.253 --> 08:27.506
You never die
and you always want something.

08:30.218 --> 08:32.093
I need you to look
at these photographs.

08:32.261 --> 08:36.056
Tell me if you recognize anybody.
I know it's been a long time but....

08:41.896 --> 08:43.563
[TARISSA SIGHS]

08:48.569 --> 08:50.111
No.

08:50.947 --> 08:52.697
Nobody. Sorry.

08:52.865 --> 08:55.951
Because one of them may be involved
with Skynet right now.

08:56.118 --> 08:58.453
They might not even know it.

09:07.630 --> 09:08.755
Sorry to bother you.

09:10.174 --> 09:12.175
I'll leave you alone.

09:14.262 --> 09:16.304
The fourth photo.

09:16.889 --> 09:18.181
The young one.

09:18.891 --> 09:21.309
His name is Andrew Goode.

09:21.477 --> 09:22.978
Andy.

09:23.187 --> 09:25.480
He was an intern at Cyberdyne
one summer.

09:27.108 --> 09:29.317
Miles liked him.

09:32.321 --> 09:33.655
Is he going to die too?

09:35.283 --> 09:38.451
Is that what happens now? He dies?

09:38.828 --> 09:40.745
I don't know.

09:42.790 --> 09:43.832
I hope not.

09:45.835 --> 09:49.004
Well, if he does,
just make sure it matters.

09:49.213 --> 09:51.673
Make sure it's not in vain.

09:54.135 --> 09:56.344
No one dies in vain.

10:13.362 --> 10:16.698
Agent Ellison.
They told me you were coming.

10:16.866 --> 10:19.326
But I told them the last time
you worked a scene...

10:19.493 --> 10:21.703
...Hoover was cross-dressing
at Quantico.

10:23.789 --> 10:25.165
Ballistics.

10:25.333 --> 10:27.834
I can already tell you mine are bigger.

10:28.961 --> 10:34.174
Same gun that killed your boys here
killed one of my CI's. Enrique Salzia.

10:34.342 --> 10:36.343
What's the connection?

10:36.636 --> 10:39.137
He made fake paper.
Your guys had fake paper.

10:39.305 --> 10:42.974
Hope you're not selling the terrorist-cell
theory because I'm not buying it.

10:43.142 --> 10:45.810
-Why not?
-Look at the print report.

10:45.978 --> 10:50.273
Cal. ID, NCIC, CDP, Interpol.
There's nothing here.

10:50.816 --> 10:54.152
These guys were drug dealers.
Small-time.

10:54.320 --> 10:56.738
Definitely not worth
you putting your tie on...

10:56.906 --> 10:59.366
...and breaking open
your Thomas Guide.

10:59.909 --> 11:03.203
Oh, yeah. We see this every day.

11:03.371 --> 11:05.372
You didn't find that curious?

11:05.539 --> 11:08.083
Why would anyone wire a safe
directly into the power?

11:08.292 --> 11:10.919
Why's the sky blue, Ellison?
Don't overthink it.

11:11.087 --> 11:15.173
The guys were druggies. They're not
rocket scientists, not terrorists.

11:15.341 --> 11:17.384
Your guy sold my guys paper.

11:17.551 --> 11:20.095
My guys whacked your guy
to cover their tracks.

11:20.304 --> 11:22.764
Go back to your office.
Your desk misses you.

11:23.683 --> 11:26.518
Right. Good one.

11:27.937 --> 11:29.104
[SIGHS]

11:30.690 --> 11:34.442
Somebody came back here
for whatever was in that safe.

11:34.610 --> 11:37.779
They're out there.
And I'm gonna find them.

11:51.961 --> 11:53.628
DOCTOR:
Hey, buddy, wait.

11:54.213 --> 11:55.839
You can't go in there.

12:45.473 --> 12:46.973
Hey. Hey.

12:47.141 --> 12:48.516
[GRUNTING]

12:55.816 --> 12:57.567
ANDY:
All right. Uh, the receipt's in the bag.

12:57.735 --> 12:59.569
Let me know if you have
any problems.

12:59.737 --> 13:02.739
You shouldn't have any problems
setting up the-- The-- You know.

13:03.365 --> 13:06.785
-You should be pretty happy.
MAN: Cool, that's so....

13:09.538 --> 13:11.706
ANDY: Let me know
if you have any problems with it.

13:11.874 --> 13:14.125
-Enjoy.
MAN: Thank you.

13:14.293 --> 13:16.044
ANDY:
Have a good day.

13:21.258 --> 13:22.550
ANDY:
Can I help you?

13:22.927 --> 13:24.552
No.

13:25.930 --> 13:28.681
Andy. Just looking.

13:29.725 --> 13:32.227
You just kept looking over
like you needed something.

13:36.232 --> 13:40.151
That's the phone. Seriously, if I was
gonna be alone on a desert island...

13:40.319 --> 13:43.321
...with only a phone for a companion
that would be the phone.

13:43.489 --> 13:45.073
Is that something you would do?

13:45.241 --> 13:46.324
[CHUCKLES]

13:46.575 --> 13:48.201
May I?

13:48.702 --> 13:50.036
Got a four-meg camera...

13:50.204 --> 13:53.832
...texting-- True texting too.
Not that SMS cartoon-bubble junk.

13:53.999 --> 13:55.917
3G data access, 10 gigs free music...

13:56.085 --> 13:59.003
...six hours of talk time
and 36 standby on your battery.

14:01.674 --> 14:03.716
What happens if I press
these numbers here?

14:04.593 --> 14:07.095
-Excuse me?
-These numbers? One through nine?

14:08.764 --> 14:11.224
If I press seven of them
will someone talk to me...

14:11.392 --> 14:13.226
...through the ear part up here?

14:14.103 --> 14:16.896
Uh.... Yeah.

14:17.356 --> 14:19.983
Okay. I'll take three.

14:26.740 --> 14:29.909
[CELL PHONE RINGING]

14:34.999 --> 14:37.417
-Hello?
ANDY [ON PHONE]: Hi.

14:39.503 --> 14:40.962
Are you calling me?

14:41.130 --> 14:43.923
Uh, I was just following up
to make sure everything's okay.

14:44.133 --> 14:48.303
-I just left the store.
ANDY: I know.

14:49.722 --> 14:51.973
Okay. Do you wanna have dinner
with me tonight?

14:52.141 --> 14:53.641
No.

14:53.809 --> 14:55.602
Well, you answered too quickly.

14:55.769 --> 14:58.271
Hear me out.
Just give me one minute.

14:59.773 --> 15:02.025
-Thirty seconds?
-Talk fast.

15:02.192 --> 15:06.404
Okay, first let me clear up the whole
desert-island-and-a-cell-phone thing.

15:06.572 --> 15:09.115
-It seems strange if you picture it.
-I wasn't.

15:09.283 --> 15:11.659
Right. Why would you?
It's an asinine sales pitch.

15:11.827 --> 15:15.288
Nowhere to plug in the phone.
It would be worth less than a rock...

15:15.456 --> 15:17.957
...when the battery died.
Couldn't even use it to open a coconut.

15:18.167 --> 15:21.502
-This is you selling yourself?
-Selling myself? I don't know.

15:21.670 --> 15:25.798
There's something immoral
about the whole selling process.

15:25.966 --> 15:28.426
-And yet, that's your job.
-Part-time.

15:28.594 --> 15:32.555
And I'm not very good at it. So I'm
actually less immoral than the average--

15:33.807 --> 15:36.017
Anyway. Um....

15:37.227 --> 15:38.728
Where was I?

15:38.896 --> 15:41.272
-You're right.
-About what?

15:42.191 --> 15:44.192
I answered too quick.

15:51.283 --> 15:54.243
-Mr. Baum?
-Yes?

15:54.411 --> 15:56.287
Take your seat, please.

16:00.834 --> 16:02.627
-Hi.
-Hi.

16:02.795 --> 16:07.006
Okay. Paper and pencil out.
Time for a pop quiz.

16:13.389 --> 16:14.931
Here.

16:15.099 --> 16:16.182
[KNOCKING ON DOOR]

16:16.350 --> 16:17.976
TEACHER:
Come in.

16:18.435 --> 16:19.727
[KNOCKING ON DOOR]

16:20.521 --> 16:22.814
I said come on in.

16:23.357 --> 16:24.607
[CHATTERING]

16:25.567 --> 16:26.859
I'm transferring in.

16:28.779 --> 16:32.115
MAN 1: That's what I'm talking about.
MAN 2: What's up with that?

16:33.117 --> 16:35.493
TEACHER:
Okay. Any open seat.

16:41.500 --> 16:44.961
JOHN: What part about "Don't act like a
freak" didn't you understand?

16:45.504 --> 16:47.046
Sit down.

16:53.971 --> 16:55.847
[DOG BARKING]

17:14.867 --> 17:16.951
[SPANISH RAP MUSIC PLAYING]

17:18.954 --> 17:20.371
JAMES: So.
-So.

17:20.539 --> 17:24.417
Like I said on the phone, your sweet
Uncle Enrique lived a colorful life.

17:24.585 --> 17:26.669
One we have not yet painted in full.

17:26.837 --> 17:28.588
You grow apart.

17:28.797 --> 17:31.674
Every day's a new adventure.
Who can keep up?

17:31.842 --> 17:33.176
[INHALES SHARPLY]

17:36.680 --> 17:38.931
I got an uncle who's like a father.

17:39.099 --> 17:42.393
I also got one who's like a stranger.
How about you two?

17:42.561 --> 17:44.979
More like an aunt. Chatty, chatty.

17:45.147 --> 17:46.397
[BOTH LAUGHING]

17:46.607 --> 17:50.526
All right. So you're not too close.

17:51.028 --> 17:53.988
But he did call you three times
the day he was murdered.

17:54.156 --> 17:57.492
-What did you chat about?
-Those Lakers.

17:57.659 --> 18:01.954
-Really? What about them?
-Kobe. He's the bomb.

18:02.122 --> 18:04.457
I always thought he was a ball hog.

18:04.625 --> 18:07.919
He's all alone, man.
He's got no one else who can shoot.

18:08.087 --> 18:10.463
Is that you, Carlos?

18:11.048 --> 18:13.174
Now that your uncle's dead?

18:13.884 --> 18:14.967
You all alone?

18:15.969 --> 18:17.637
Yeah.

18:18.180 --> 18:20.181
All these boys can shoot.

18:22.434 --> 18:24.102
[LAUGHS]

18:31.902 --> 18:35.029
-I didn't kill my uncle.
-No.

18:35.948 --> 18:39.158
And you're too smart
to know nothing about who did.

18:43.747 --> 18:45.873
I'll be in touch.

18:57.678 --> 19:01.472
No, I know. The guy's 18 months
ahead of the Germans.

19:01.640 --> 19:04.517
Yeah, well, I would
if I had that kind of grant money.

19:04.685 --> 19:07.145
No, I'm not saying
the guy's a complete idiot.

19:07.312 --> 19:09.647
It's not exactly
avant-garde science, is it?

19:09.815 --> 19:12.483
Why don't they give money
to people on the cutting edge?

19:12.651 --> 19:14.277
But they never do. They never--

19:14.444 --> 19:16.320
[FOOTSTEPS]

19:20.909 --> 19:22.618
[CHOKING]

19:29.918 --> 19:31.586
Hey.

19:32.462 --> 19:36.716
-How was school?
-I have a metal plate in my head.

19:36.925 --> 19:38.593
She's gonna need a note.

19:38.760 --> 19:41.053
-I meant you, not her.
JOHN: Yeah, fine.

19:41.221 --> 19:42.680
SARAH:
You're not gonna give me anything?

19:42.848 --> 19:43.931
We went, we learned.

19:44.099 --> 19:47.977
I didn't get killed and she didn't kill
anybody. It was a pretty good first day.

19:48.145 --> 19:49.812
-What about you, did you go?
SARAH: I did.

19:49.980 --> 19:51.856
JOHN: How was she?
Surprised you weren't dead?

19:52.024 --> 19:53.983
More like disappointed.

19:54.193 --> 19:55.985
She ID'd
one of the safe-house photos.

19:56.153 --> 19:58.070
-Intern at Cyberdyne.
JOHN: Really?

19:58.238 --> 20:01.949
What does he do? Work in a lab or build
rocket guidance systems or something?

20:02.117 --> 20:05.286
-Cell phone salesman.
-Shut up.

20:05.454 --> 20:07.872
Cell phone salesman,
and not a very good one.

20:08.040 --> 20:09.290
CAMERON:
These need to be cleaned.

20:13.128 --> 20:14.754
JOHN: Okay, so about
the cell-phone guy.

20:14.963 --> 20:17.298
I'm having dinner with him tonight.

20:18.258 --> 20:22.845
-Dinner? You mean, like a date?
-Not a date.

20:23.472 --> 20:25.681
Are you going to kill him?

20:26.099 --> 20:29.602
Kill him?
I don't know the first thing about him.

20:29.770 --> 20:34.565
He interned at Cyberdyne in college.
His photo's in a pile of photos.

20:37.736 --> 20:39.570
Nobody dies till I say so.

20:42.491 --> 20:43.991
Tell her.

20:44.409 --> 20:47.161
People die all the time.
They won't wait for her.

20:52.501 --> 20:54.210
I fooled you again.

20:54.378 --> 20:56.254
[EXHALES]

21:02.803 --> 21:04.637
Who are you?

21:05.597 --> 21:10.434
How did you find me?
What-- What do you want?

21:11.019 --> 21:13.354
Are you a veteran?
Is that what this is about?

21:14.856 --> 21:16.857
