22:11.413 --> 22:13.622
TERMINATOR:
Can you do it?

22:16.585 --> 22:19.170
Well, I'd have to go to my lab.

22:19.338 --> 22:25.509
There's a whole mix of growth rates.
TGF-beta, PDGF, EGF--

22:25.677 --> 22:27.094
I'd need--

22:27.262 --> 22:30.222
You know, there's a lot of equipment.

22:30.390 --> 22:34.435
Oh, and blood.
We need at least 20 units.

22:34.644 --> 22:39.065
-Preferably with tissues comprised--
TERMINATOR: I brought my own.

22:42.069 --> 22:44.195
TERMINATOR:
Can you do it?

22:46.615 --> 22:48.199
Yes.

22:52.120 --> 22:53.662
Yes, I can.

22:56.750 --> 22:58.209
SARAH [VOICE-OVER]:
In 1943...

22:58.377 --> 23:00.461
...the German physicist
Werner Heisenberg...

23:00.629 --> 23:03.756
...delivered a physics lecture
to a packed hall in Zurich.

23:03.924 --> 23:05.966
One of the audience members
was Moe Berg...

23:06.134 --> 23:09.970
...an ex-professional baseball player
working as a spy for the OSS.

23:10.138 --> 23:13.974
Berg's task was to listen to the lecture
and determine whether the Germans...

23:14.184 --> 23:16.936
...were close to perfecting
the atomic bomb.

23:17.104 --> 23:19.146
If Berg discovered
that this was the case...

23:19.314 --> 23:21.816
...he was to wait
for Heisenberg outside the hall...

23:21.983 --> 23:24.610
...and shoot the scientist in the head.

23:28.657 --> 23:31.450
He had never killed anyone before.

23:38.125 --> 23:39.792
So what's your deal, Andy?

23:39.960 --> 23:42.920
I can't imagine you majored
in cell phone sales at college.

23:43.088 --> 23:47.758
No. No. More like Funyuns and 12 packs
of Jolt from the vintage soda store...

23:47.926 --> 23:50.261
...while my roommates and I
hacked "Zelda III"...

23:50.429 --> 23:53.305
...so the princess would say
funny lines ripped from reruns.

23:53.473 --> 23:56.016
What's that language you speak, boy?

23:56.435 --> 24:01.689
Computer science.
Caltech. Advanced Dork.

24:01.940 --> 24:06.026
And what would you do
with a computer degree from Caltech?

24:06.236 --> 24:08.154
I don't know. I never got one.

24:08.321 --> 24:10.781
-Really?
-My father died senior year.

24:10.949 --> 24:14.034
Mom went a little off the rails.
I dropped out to help.

24:14.953 --> 24:16.203
I'm sorry.

24:16.371 --> 24:20.124
No, it was a long time ago,
but thanks anyway.

24:20.292 --> 24:23.794
She's good. She married
the security guard at her bank.

24:27.883 --> 24:29.967
Do you have family?

24:30.218 --> 24:31.886
Distant.

24:33.680 --> 24:37.391
Don't take this the wrong way, but as
a cell phone salesman I think I can ask.

24:37.559 --> 24:40.561
Did you ever wanna be anything
other than a waitress?

24:40.770 --> 24:43.397
-Yes, I did.
-What was it?

24:45.233 --> 24:47.318
I can't remember.

24:52.657 --> 24:54.033
What's this, Andy?

24:57.245 --> 24:58.704
Oh, isn't it great?

25:00.081 --> 25:03.584
That is the official promotional poster
for the Kramnik-Deep Fritz match.

25:03.752 --> 25:05.336
Awesome match. Just awesome.

25:05.504 --> 25:08.088
Most people cite
the '97 Kasparov-Deep Blue...

25:08.298 --> 25:10.716
...as the watershed man-versus-machine
chess match.

25:10.884 --> 25:13.427
But, uh, Fritz would have
wiped the floor with Blue...

25:13.595 --> 25:16.013
... just like Kramnik did
with Kasparov.

25:16.181 --> 25:19.266
Besides, the other poster's
impossible to find.

25:20.227 --> 25:22.561
What is it you do, Andy?

25:24.898 --> 25:26.023
Do you wanna see?

25:27.234 --> 25:28.901
Yes, I wanna see.

25:30.612 --> 25:31.737
All right.

25:36.535 --> 25:38.285
Behold.

25:40.288 --> 25:42.206
The Turk.

25:44.876 --> 25:48.337
-The Turk?
-Well, not the original Turk.

25:48.797 --> 25:50.881
The original Turk was an automaton...

25:51.049 --> 25:55.302
...constructed and unveiled in 1770
by the Baron Wolfgang von Kempelen.

25:56.805 --> 25:58.138
It played chess.

25:58.306 --> 26:01.225
Is that what your Turk does?
It plays chess?

26:01.393 --> 26:05.312
I know that sounds boring as hell.
Most people think so.

26:05.480 --> 26:07.606
But maybe I should put it this way:

26:07.774 --> 26:11.986
My Turk plays chess at a level
that could defeat every human player...

26:12.153 --> 26:15.072
...that has ever lived
and probably ever will live.

26:15.240 --> 26:17.992
That's not bragging.
A number of AIs can do that now.

26:18.159 --> 26:20.327
But the AI chess platform
is very valuable...

26:20.495 --> 26:22.955
...for artificial intelligence developers.

26:24.583 --> 26:26.166
What?

26:26.376 --> 26:28.294
I thought I saw someone outside.

26:29.254 --> 26:30.921
[CRICKETS CHIRPING]

26:44.269 --> 26:46.478
Uh, yeah, it's a prowler.

26:47.814 --> 26:49.648
Uh, back porch. It's the police.

26:49.816 --> 26:52.026
There's been break-ins
in the neighborhood.

26:52.193 --> 26:53.485
-My--
SARAH: I have to go, Andy.

26:53.653 --> 26:57.531
No, Sarah, wait.
Uh, it's 165 Mesrow. Sarah!

27:00.702 --> 27:03.037
Again, what did it look like?

27:03.371 --> 27:05.914
What did it look like?
Who cares what it looked like?

27:06.082 --> 27:08.042
It was a rack of computer equipment.

27:08.209 --> 27:10.544
Okay, but was there
obvious network access?

27:10.712 --> 27:13.881
-Do you know what kind of bandwidth?
-You're joking.

27:14.049 --> 27:16.216
What about power supply?
Was there a cooling element?

27:16.384 --> 27:18.385
-Like a fan or something?
-John--

27:18.553 --> 27:20.888
I'm just trying to get a sense
of the horsepower.

27:21.056 --> 27:25.059
I wanna know if this thing
was a dinky little homemade soap box...

27:25.226 --> 27:27.394
...or if it was a full-fledged
Al platform...

27:28.063 --> 27:32.232
...capable of learning and growing
and taking on other applications.

27:32.400 --> 27:34.610
It plays chess.

27:35.070 --> 27:36.403
So did Einstein.

27:41.743 --> 27:44.620
Have you ever heard
of the Singularity?

27:46.748 --> 27:50.084
It's a point in time
where machines become so smart...

27:50.251 --> 27:55.089
...that they're capable of making smarter
versions of themselves without our help.

27:57.926 --> 28:00.928
That's pretty much the time
we can kiss our asses goodbye.

28:02.263 --> 28:04.264
Unless we stop it.

28:06.267 --> 28:07.601
Like you said you would.

28:19.239 --> 28:22.783
So I caught a break on a set
of fingerprints from our drug dealers.

28:22.951 --> 28:25.828
I wanted to see your face
when I laid that on you.

28:26.621 --> 28:31.083
See, the only fingerprint database
I hadn't checked was kid prints.

28:31.292 --> 28:34.461
Ha, ha. That's no joke. That's him.
That's one of your dead terrorists.

28:34.629 --> 28:40.676
A black-haired, brown-eyed, 35-pound,
4-year-old boy living in Canton, Ohio.

28:43.680 --> 28:44.805
[SIGHS]

28:45.765 --> 28:47.766
And that's the look I wanted to see.

28:53.606 --> 28:55.315
JAMES:
Hold up.

28:58.820 --> 29:02.489
Did your crime-scene guys
find any peculiar blood?

29:02.657 --> 29:06.285
I think they got all the peculiar
they could stomach with these prints.

29:06.453 --> 29:10.205
Lab says some blood evidence found
at my CI crime scene is almost human.

29:10.957 --> 29:13.000
Except there's no
red blood cells present.

29:14.335 --> 29:16.503
I wanna see the blood evidence
from your guys.

29:18.715 --> 29:19.840
I'll get back to you.

29:20.633 --> 29:22.801
You're gonna double check those prints,
right?

29:22.969 --> 29:24.595
On the kid in Canton?

29:25.472 --> 29:27.181
[SIGHS]

29:29.184 --> 29:30.893
Have a party.

29:34.606 --> 29:36.023
[EXHALES SHARPLY]

29:36.191 --> 29:37.524
[BEEPING]

29:37.901 --> 29:41.153
The thing I hadn't thought of,
the thing nobody thought possible...

29:41.321 --> 29:44.531
...was the use
of a synthetic oxygen carrier.

29:47.994 --> 29:52.998
By creating a synthetic spear that carries
oxygen bringing nutrients to the skin...

29:53.166 --> 29:56.752
...it obviates the need
for the marrow interaction.

29:58.713 --> 30:03.926
The real-world applications are,
well, mind-blowing.

30:18.066 --> 30:20.192
It's ready.

30:21.194 --> 30:24.905
I have a video camera.
Would it be all right if--?

30:25.073 --> 30:26.949
TERMINATOR [IN ROBOT VOICE]:
Move away.

30:48.763 --> 30:50.681
Who are you?

30:52.058 --> 30:53.934
What are you?

31:09.200 --> 31:10.701
Sarah?

31:11.494 --> 31:14.663
Didn't you get my message?
I returned your call about the results.

31:14.831 --> 31:18.834
-Yeah, I got your message.
-Yeah. You're healthy as a horse.

31:19.002 --> 31:20.335
A healthy horse.

31:20.503 --> 31:22.588
I got that from your message.

31:22.755 --> 31:24.798
I wanted to talk to you
about prevention.

31:24.966 --> 31:28.427
For cancer? What you're doing
seems to be working.

31:28.595 --> 31:29.845
Specifically.

31:30.305 --> 31:32.639
Um.... Don't smoke.

31:32.807 --> 31:37.311
Get lots of exercise. Eat leafy greens.
Don't snort asbestos.

31:38.813 --> 31:41.648
I don't mean to make light,
but you've got no risk factors.

31:41.816 --> 31:42.983
No genetic disposition.

31:43.151 --> 31:46.653
Is there anything else about your history
that I should know?

31:47.488 --> 31:48.989
No.

31:50.450 --> 31:52.659
You've got children, right?

31:53.536 --> 31:55.537
Yeah, I got two myself.

31:55.747 --> 31:59.875
You worry. You wanna make sure you're
always healthy and strong for them.

32:01.544 --> 32:06.673
Don't drive yourself crazy
chasing the future. We can't predict.

32:07.008 --> 32:10.886
You know?
We can only try and prevent.

32:21.773 --> 32:24.149
[CELL PHONE BEEPS]

32:24.359 --> 32:27.527
Andy, it's Sarah.

32:32.241 --> 32:34.368
[CHATTERING]

32:38.539 --> 32:39.665
MAN:
Forget about it.

32:45.296 --> 32:47.589
-Hey.
-Hi.

32:48.216 --> 32:50.592
-You going to chem?
-Yeah.

33:03.356 --> 33:05.857
-What is going on?
-No idea.

33:06.025 --> 33:11.405
WOMAN 1: She is such a skanky whore.
Ugh, disgusting.

33:13.408 --> 33:14.908
WOMAN 2:
Dirty whore.

33:15.243 --> 33:19.371
CHOLA: I love this color.
It's tight, right?

33:19.539 --> 33:20.747
This color's tight.

33:20.915 --> 33:23.000
-What is it?
-Rash.

33:23.167 --> 33:25.252
It's so tight.

33:25.420 --> 33:26.545
[SCOFFS]

33:26.713 --> 33:29.589
I'm a pig. I look pregnant.

33:29.757 --> 33:31.758
