33:40.184 --> 33:41.893
Bitch-whore much?

33:42.520 --> 33:43.729
I don't understand.

33:44.188 --> 33:47.441
I said, bitch-whore much?

33:49.068 --> 33:50.277
What are you looking at?

33:51.112 --> 33:52.529
I'm looking at you.

34:07.086 --> 34:11.256
[WOMAN CRYING]

34:14.427 --> 34:15.719
[BREATHES SHARPLY]

34:18.473 --> 34:20.766
You saw it, right?

34:20.933 --> 34:22.809
Right? You saw it?

34:23.478 --> 34:27.814
It's so freaking big,
and right out there.

34:29.692 --> 34:33.320
-It's freaking big.
JORDAN: Right. It is, right?

34:34.447 --> 34:36.740
Whoever's doing this
is such a jackass.

34:37.950 --> 34:41.453
I mean, who would do this?
And how would they even know?

34:41.621 --> 34:43.663
My parents.

34:43.831 --> 34:48.126
They're gonna kill me. Kill me.

34:49.087 --> 34:51.922
I mean, don't we have hall monitors?
I mean, how could someone just--

34:52.090 --> 34:54.841
[CRYING]

34:57.637 --> 34:58.845
You're upset.

35:01.015 --> 35:05.602
No kidding, I'm upset.
My life is freaking over.

35:10.525 --> 35:12.359
Here's a present.

35:14.153 --> 35:15.278
It's tight.

35:16.823 --> 35:18.698
[JORDAN CRYING]

35:24.956 --> 35:27.290
ANDY: I have to admit,
I wondered if I'd see you again.

35:27.458 --> 35:31.169
SARAH: Miracles happen every day.
ANDY: That's funny.

35:31.546 --> 35:35.382
ANDY: That was a joke, right?
SARAH: lf it was funny, it was a joke.

35:35.550 --> 35:38.885
ANDY: So the police recommended
that I put in a security system.

35:39.303 --> 35:43.056
Armed patrol, that kind of thing.
Can't really afford it, though.

35:43.266 --> 35:46.560
-You think someone wants the Turk?
-Well, eight years of my life.

35:47.145 --> 35:50.021
Not just the software.
I customized the hardware too.

35:50.189 --> 35:53.024
One month, I worked so much
on a motherboard...

35:53.192 --> 35:55.819
...that I lost my sight for three days.

35:56.279 --> 36:00.031
No, that really happened.
Those circuits are so small.

36:00.199 --> 36:03.243
A lot of the gear is actually pulled
from gaming platforms.

36:03.411 --> 36:06.580
Did you know that the military
uses them?

36:06.789 --> 36:11.042
Yeah, I've got the guts of three Xboxes
and four PlayStations, daisy-chained.

36:11.210 --> 36:15.172
Plus some seriously modded-out code
that I swear came to me in a dream.

36:15.923 --> 36:19.551
And all this to beat another computer
at chess?

36:20.511 --> 36:23.722
None of this to beat another computer
at chess.

36:24.432 --> 36:26.099
Then what?

36:27.059 --> 36:29.019
What are you doing?

36:30.438 --> 36:32.814
Would you believe me if I told you
Turk has moods?

36:33.316 --> 36:36.610
Obviously not in the sense
that you and I understand mood...

36:36.819 --> 36:41.907
...but sometimes I'll feed it a particular
chess problem, and it'll solve it one way.

36:42.074 --> 36:45.410
The next day, I feed it the same problem
and it solves it differently.

36:46.120 --> 36:48.955
Once in a while,
it can't even solve it at all.

36:49.290 --> 36:52.626
-Do you know why it does that?
-No.

36:52.919 --> 36:57.881
Yeah, neither do I.
Someday, I'm gonna figure it out.

36:58.341 --> 37:01.468
-Someday, Turk will tell me.
-You talk about it like it's human.

37:03.054 --> 37:04.387
Well, you never know.

37:06.641 --> 37:11.269
What? Too far? What is it?

37:13.397 --> 37:14.940
Nothing.

37:16.484 --> 37:18.360
Nothing at all.

37:24.158 --> 37:26.243
[CHATTERING]

37:28.120 --> 37:31.748
-Do you like this color on me?
-What?

37:31.916 --> 37:35.669
-I'm a bitch-whore.
-What?

37:36.003 --> 37:38.004
I have a new friend.

37:38.172 --> 37:40.966
Did she tell you,
you were a bitch-whore?

37:41.133 --> 37:43.176
No. She cried.

37:44.345 --> 37:46.429
Wait. What?

37:48.808 --> 37:51.476
Okay, what the hell is this thing?

37:51.644 --> 37:53.937
MAN:
Jumper. Outside the gym.

37:54.438 --> 37:56.356
[CHATTERING]

38:04.490 --> 38:05.991
MAN 1:
Yo, man, check it out.

38:11.622 --> 38:13.957
MAN 2: Jump! Jump!
WOMAN 1: Shut up.

38:14.125 --> 38:16.876
